</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1878,2012]" lastBlockId="12.[151,1436,150,250]" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="69" pageId="11" pageNumber="68">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1893" box="[151,312,1878,1904]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Ceroplastodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,312,1878,1904]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="68">Ceroplastodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a New World genus, with the 
<typeStatus box="[677,725,1878,1904]" pageId="11" pageNumber="68">type</typeStatus>
species found in 
<collectingCountry box="[922,1008,1878,1904]" name="Mexico" pageId="11" pageNumber="68">Mexico</collectingCountry>
and some southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1232,1309,1878,1904]" name="United States of America" pageId="11" pageNumber="68">U.S.A.</collectingCountry>
states; five other 
<taxonomicName box="[216,464,1914,1940]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Ceroplastodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[216,377,1914,1940]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="68">Ceroplastodes</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
occur in the New World. Of the non-New World species, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Green, 1900)" baseAuthorityName="Green" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[1112,1436,1914,1940]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Ceroplastodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melaleucae">
<emphasis box="[1112,1273,1914,1940]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="68">C. melaleucae</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Green, E. E." box="[1287,1428,1914,1940]" pageId="11" pageNumber="68" pagination="9 - 14" refId="ref11085" refString="Green, E. E. (1900) Descriptions of new Victorian Coccidae. The Victorian Naturalist, 1, 9 - 14." type="journal article" year="1900">Green, 1900</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
occurs in 
<collectingCountry box="[259,362,1950,1976]" name="Australia" pageId="11" pageNumber="68">Australia</collectingCountry>
and is not congeneric with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1893" box="[672,786,1950,1976]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Ceroplastodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dugesii">
<emphasis box="[672,786,1950,1976]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="68">C. dugesii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Gullan &amp; Hodgson in prep.); 
<taxonomicName authority="Yousuf &amp; Shafee, 1988" authorityName="Yousuf &amp; Shafee" authorityYear="1988" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Ceroplastodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wandoorensis">
<emphasis box="[1133,1321,1950,1976]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="68">C. wandoorensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Yousuf, M. &amp; Shafee, S. A." pageId="11" pageNumber="68" pagination="57 - 63" refId="ref12107" refString="Yousuf, M. &amp; Shafee, S. A. (1988) Four new species of Coccidae (Homoptera) from Andaman Islands. Indian Journal of Systematic Entomology, 5, 57 - 63." type="journal article" year="1988">Yousuf &amp; Shafee, 1988</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, is only known from the Andaman Is. and is very unlikely to belong to 
<emphasis box="[1076,1244,1986,2012]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="68">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1893" box="[1076,1239,1986,2012]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Ceroplastodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Ceroplastodes</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
whilst 
<taxonomicName authority="Laing, 1925" authorityName="Laing" authorityYear="1925" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Ceroplastodes" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="69" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ritchiei">
<emphasis box="[1324,1436,1986,2012]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="68">C. ritchiei</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Laing, F." box="[151,288,150,177]" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" pagination="51 - 66" refId="ref11640" refString="Laing, F. (1925) Descriptions of some new genera and species of Coccidae. Bulletin of Entomological Research, 16, 51 - 66. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0007485300056157" type="journal article" year="1925">Laing, 1925</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Bellio, 1939" authorityName="Bellio" authorityYear="1939" box="[346,629,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Ceroplastodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zavatarii">
<emphasis box="[346,481,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="69">C. zavatarii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bellio, G." box="[489,629,151,177]" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" pagination="225 - 239" refId="ref10597" refString="Bellio, G. (1939) Hemiptera, Coccidae. Missione Biologica nel Paese dei Borana. Raccolte Zoologiche. Roma, 3, 225 - 239." type="journal article" year="1939">Bellio, 1939</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
are known only from Africa. Both of these species are fully described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hodgson, C. J." box="[187,370,187,213]" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" pagination="49 - 61" refId="ref11385" refString="Hodgson, C. J. (1971) The species assigned to the genus Ceroplastodes (Homoptera: Coccoidea) in the Ethiopian region. Journal of Entomology (B) Taxonomy, 40, 49 - 61. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 3113.1971. tb 00104. x" type="journal article" year="1971">Hodgson (1971)</bibRefCitation>
. Neither of them is congeneric with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1893" box="[779,892,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Ceroplastodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dugesii">
<emphasis box="[779,892,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="69">C. dugesii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and here both are transferred to 
<taxonomicName authority="Williams &amp; Watson (1990)" authorityName="Williams &amp; Watson" authorityYear="1990" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Drepanococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1265,1436,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="69">Drepanococcus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Williams, D. J. &amp; Watson, G. W." box="[151,446,223,249]" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" refId="ref12059" refString="Williams, D. J. &amp; Watson, G. W. (1990) The Scale Insects of the Tropical South Pacific Region. Pt. 3. The Soft Scales (Coccidae) and Other Families. CAB International, Wallingford, 267 pp." type="book" year="1990">Williams &amp; Watson (1990)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Laing)" authorityName="Hodgson" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Hodgson" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[482,684,223,250]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Ceroplastodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ritchiei" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[482,595,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="69">D. ritchiei</emphasis>
(Laing)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[690,816,223,249]" pageId="12" pageNumber="69">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[690,816,223,249]" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[830,895,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="12.[151,250,2000,2024]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,273,1977]" captionTargetId="figure-80@12.[151,1436,273,1977]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 8. Drepanococcus ritchiei (Laing). Adult female. After Hodgson 1971" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5222991" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5222991/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="69">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bellio)" authorityName="Hodgson" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Hodgson" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[957,1187,223,250]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Drepanococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zavattarii" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[957,1095,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="69">D. zavattarii</emphasis>
(Bellio)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1193,1334,222,249]" pageId="12" pageNumber="69">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1193,1319,223,249]" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
</emphasis>
<figureCitation box="[1334,1400,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1930,1954]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,188,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-16@13.[151,1436,181,1907]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 9. Drepanococcus zavattarii (Bellio). Adult female.After Hodgson 1971." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5222995" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5222995/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="69">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
